                               ### devops pro notes
############# common issues faced on github
1. Non-Fast-Forward (push rejected)
Remote ahead of local.
git pull origin main
Resolve conflicts if any.
git push origin main
​

2. Auth Failed (access rights)
No/wrong credentials.
Generate PAT (github.com/settings/tokens).
git remote set-url origin https://user:PAT@github.com/repo.git
git push
​

3. Credential Prompt Always
No caching.
git config --global credential.helper manager-core
Push once (enter user:PAT).
Cached in Windows Credential Manager.
​

4. Merge Conflicts
Pull shows conflicts.
Edit conflicted files (remove <<<< >>>>).
git add .
git commit → push.
​

5. Fatal: Not a Git Repo
Wrong dir.
git init or cd /path/to/repo
git status
Proceed with add/commit/push.
####################################################################
## BRANCHES

git branch                   → List branches (* = current)
git branch -r                → List remote branches

git branch new-branch         → Create new-branch from current
git branch -m new-name        → Rename current to new-name (-M force)

git branch -d old-branch      → Delete old-branch (safe)
git branch -D old-branch      → Force delete old-branch


